12 SECTION 3.(b) G.S. 7B-303 reads as rewritten:
13 "§ 7B-303. Interference with assessment.
14 (a) If any person obstructs or interferes with an assessment required by G.S. 7B-302, the
15 director may sign and file a petition naming that person as respondent and requesting an order
16 directing the respondent to cease the obstruction or interference. The petition shall contain the
17 name and date of birth and address of the juvenile who is the subject of the assessment; shall
18 include a concise statement of the basis for initiating the assessment, shall specifically describe
19 the conduct alleged to constitute obstruction of or interference with the assessment; and shall be
20 verified. If the legal counsel for the department has not also signed the petition, the director shall
21 attest that the petition has been reviewed by the legal counsel for the department.
22 …
23 (c) Upon filing of the petition, the court shall schedule a hearing to be held not less than
24 five days after service of the petition and summons on the respondent. Service of the petition and
25 summons and notice of hearing shall be made as provided by the Rules of Civil Procedure on the
26 respondent; the juvenile's parent, guardian, custodian, or caretaker; and any other person
27 determined by the court to be a necessary party. If at the hearing on the petition the court finds
28 by clear, cogent, clear and convincing evidence that the respondent, without lawful excuse, has
29 obstructed or interfered with an assessment required by G.S. 7B-302, the court may order the
30 respondent to cease such obstruction or interference. The burden of proof shall be on the
31 petitioner.
32 …."
33 SECTION 3.(c) G.S. 7B-403 reads as rewritten:
34 "§ 7B-403. Receipt of reports; filing of petition.
35 (a) All reports concerning a juvenile alleged to be abused, neglected, or dependent shall
36 be referred to the director of the department of social services for screening. Thereafter, if it is
37 determined by the director that a report should be filed as a petition, the petition shall be drawn
38 drafted or reviewed by the director, legal counsel for the department, signed by the director, and
39 verified before an official authorized to administer oaths, and filed by the clerk, recording the
40 date of filing. If the legal counsel for the department has not also signed the petition, the director
41 shall attest that the petition has been reviewed by the legal counsel for the department.
42 (b) A decision of the director of social services not to file a report as a petition shall be
43 reviewed by the prosecutor Division if review is requested pursuant to G.S. 7B-305."
44 SECTION 3.(d) G.S. 7B-503(b) reads as rewritten:
45 "(b) Whenever a petition is filed under G.S. 7B-302(d1), the court shall rule on the petition
46 prior to returning the child to a home where the alleged abuser or abusers are or have been present.
47 If the court finds that the alleged abuser or abusers have a history of violent behavior against
48 people, the court shall order the alleged abuser or abusers to submit to a complete mental health
49 evaluation by a licensed psychologist or psychiatrist. The court may order the alleged abuser or
50 abusers to pay the cost of any mental health evaluation required under this section."
