19 SECTION 10.(a) Article 6 of Subchapter I of Chapter 7B of the General Statutes is
20 amended by adding a new section to read:
21 "§ 7B-604. Legal counsel for department.
22 (a) The county department of social services shall be represented by legal counsel for the
23 department in proceedings governed by this Subchapter.
24 (b) Prior to representing the county department of social services in proceedings
25 governed by this Subchapter, an attorney shall complete a minimum of six hours of training
26 addressing State and federal child welfare law and procedures.
27 (c) The Division in consultation with (i) representatives of county directors and (ii) legal
28 counsel for the department who are department attorneys shall establish ongoing training and
29 practice standards that apply to legal counsel for the department."
30 SECTION 10.(b) Section 10(a) of this act becomes effective on April 1, 2026.
31 SECTION 11.(a) G.S. 7B-903.1 reads as rewritten:
32 "§ 7B-903.1. Juvenile placed in custody of a department of social services.
33 …
34 (c) If a juvenile is removed from the home and placed in the custody or placement
35 responsibility of a county department of social services, the director shall not allow unsupervised
36 visitation with or return physical custody of the juvenile to the parent, guardian, custodian, or
37 caretaker from whom the juvenile was removed without a hearing at which the court finds that
38 the juvenile will receive proper care and supervision in a safe home. Before a county department
39 of social services may recommend unsupervised visits or return of physical custody of the
40 juvenile juvenile, whichever occurs first, to the parent, guardian, custodian, or caretaker from
41 whom the juvenile was removed, a county department of social services shall first observe that
42 parent, guardian, custodian, or caretaker with the juvenile for at least two visits that support the
43 recommendation. Each observation visit shall consist of an observation of not less than one hour
44 with the juvenile, shall be conducted at least seven days apart, and shall occur within 30 days of
45 the hearing at which the department of social services makes the recommendation. A department
46 of social services shall provide documentation of any observation visits that it conducts to the
47 court for its consideration as to whether unsupervised visits or physical custody custody,
48 whichever occurs first, should be granted to the parent, guardian, custodian, or caretaker from
49 whom the juvenile was removed.
50 …."
